result.name: Palki Indian Restaurant

reviews.text:
Updated review:
I’ve eaten here for lunch a few times now and always thought it was okay, except the last time they forgot our drinks and my curry arrived with large piece of a PLASTIC BAG in it. When I showed the server she was apologetic, but she simply said, “Sorry, the kitchen is busy right now.” No refund or discount on my meal, which I didn’t finish, and no replacement. I won’t be back again.

Old review:
Stopped in for lunch this week and got this scrumptious little thali platter. It had three small pots of curry, a crispy samosa, raita, rice, fresh naan, and was served with soup to start. It wasn't the absolute best curry I've had, but it was tasty and I thought it was a nice place for lunch.
Nice food house to taste Indian dishes. A complete experience of north Indian cuisine. Ambiance much closer to Indian kitchen with western touch. Staff are cheerful and service quality is at best...
Absolutely delicious food, fantastic taste and totally reminded me of India. Thanks so much for making the taste just perfect! 👌👌👌
Real authentic northern indian food? You got it all in here. Even the music came from the same region. Worth to try!

I love this Indian place! Service is great, we usually order waaaaay too much! Palak paneer, kormas, puri naan etc etc. Well seasoned food. Chicken tandoori was succulent and very tasty. I always get the mango lassi. My favorite Indian place in Hong Kong :)
